data.chText: 分配（某物）；分派，布置（工作、任务等）
data.enText: to give sb sth that they can use, or some work or responsibility

data.chText: 这两间大教室分配给了我们。
data.enText: The two large classrooms have been assigned to us.

data.chText: 老师给每个儿童布置的作业都不相同。
data.enText: The teacher assigned a different task to each of the children.

data.chText: 我们分得了这两间大教室。

data.hoverText: 动词+名词短语+名词短语

data.enText: We have been assigned the two large classrooms.

data.chText: 老师给每个儿童都布置了不同的作业。
data.enText: The teacher assigned each of the children a different task.
to provide a person for a particular task or position

data.chText: 他们指派了最优秀的人担任这项工作。
data.enText: They've assigned their best man to the job.

data.chText: 英国军队被派遣协助维持和平。

data.hoverText: 动词+名词短语+带to的不定式

data.enText: British forces have been assigned to help with peacekeeping.
to send a person to work under the authority of sb or in a particular group
I was assigned to B platoon.

data.chText: 确定（价值、功能、时间、地点）
data.enText: to say that sth has a particular value or function, or happens at a particular time or place

data.chText: 给每类信息分别确定一种颜色。
data.enText: Assign a different colour to each different type of information.

data.chText: 这幅画的年代确定不了。

data.hoverText: 动词+名词短语+名词短语

data.enText: The painting cannot be assigned an exact date.
to say that your property or rights now belong to sb else

data.chText: 协议规定将版权转让给出版商。
data.enText: The agreement assigns copyright to the publisher.

simple_means.memory_skill: as 加强 + sign 信号 → 一再给人信号 → 指定 → 指定人后分配工作 → 分配

tr: select something or someone for a specific purpose
example: The teacher assigned him to lead his classmates in the exercise
We attributed this quotation to Shakespeare
People impute great cleverness to cats

tr: decide as to where something belongs in a scheme
example: The biologist assigned the mushroom to the proper class
She put too much emphasis on her the last statement
He put all his efforts into this job
The teacher put an interesting twist to the interpretation of the story

tr: give an assignment to (a person) to a post, or assign a task to (a person)

value.def: If you assign a piece of work to someone, you give them the work to do.

example.ex: When I taught, I would assign a topic to children which they would write about...
example.tran: 我教课时会给孩子们布置一个题目，让他们就这个题目写点东西。

example.ex: Later in the year, she'll assign them research papers...
example.tran: 今年晚些时候，她将给他们指定研究论文。

example.ex: When teachers assign homework, students usually feel an obligation to do it.
example.tran: 当老师布置家庭作业的时候，学生们通常觉得做作业是分内之事。

value.def: If you assign something to someone, you say that it is for their use.

example.ex: The selling broker is then required to assign a portion of the commission to the buyer broker...
example.tran: 卖方经纪人须随后将部分佣金分给买方经纪人。

example.ex: He assigned her all his land in Ireland.
example.tran: 他把自己在爱尔兰的所有土地都转给了她。

value.def: If someone is assigned to a particular place, group, or person, they are sent there, usually in order to work at that place or for that person.

example.ex: I was assigned to Troop A of the 10th Cavalry...
example.tran: 我被派往第10骑兵队的A连。

example.ex: Did you choose Russia or were you simply assigned there?...
example.tran: 你是自己选择去的俄罗斯还是就是被派到那里的？

example.ex: Each of us was assigned a minder, someone who looked after us.
example.tran: 我们每个人都被派了一个看护人来照顾我们。

value.def: If you assign a particular function or value to someone or something, you say they have it.

example.ex: Under Mr. Harel's system, each business must assign a value to each job...
example.tran: 根据哈雷尔先生的体系，每个企业必须赋予每份工作一定的价值。

example.ex: Assign the letters of the alphabet their numerical values — A equals 1, B equals 2, etc.
example.tran: 给字母表里的每个字母赋予相应的数值——A等于1，B等于2，等等。
